<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,1175,1881]" lastBlockId="10.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Discussion: This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[823,965,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugatulus">
<emphasis box="[823,965,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. rugatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the two may well only be geographic variants of a single species. More extensive collections must be made between 
<collectingCountry box="[264,392,324,350]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[449,576,324,350]" name="Guatemala" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
to determine the relationship of these two forms.
</paragraph>
